\texttt{flask\_app} in the shipped benchmark run produces no
retry-pattern or circuit-breaker POLICY mappings (the fixture's request
handlers are thin flask routes without \texttt{@retry} decorators), so
removing this family has zero measured effect. \texttt{calculator}
contains no resilience patterns and is unchanged. The resilience family
sits at the lowest confidence band in
\texttt{../cogant/docs/evaluation/CALIBRATION.md} (\(0.65\) for
\texttt{SingletonAccessRule}, \(0.70\) for \texttt{RetryPatternRule} /
\texttt{ErrorBoundaryRule}) and is documented as the lowest-precision
family in the calibration backlog; on resilience-heavy fixtures (the
synthetic \texttt{event\_pipeline} \texttt{RetryableEventHandler} class)
the family contributes approximately one to two POLICY mappings per such
class. \\
